Miep or l will be up each day
to bring you food and news.

92
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,520
Come, Miep, we must go.

93
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:09,400
-Goodbye.
FRANK: Goodbye, Mr. Kraler.

94
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,880
EDITH :
How can we thank you?

95
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:18,080
l never thought l'd live to see the day
when a man like Mr. Frank...

96
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:22,880
...would have to go into hiding.
When you think of it....

97
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:26,640
FRANK: Goodbye.
PETRONELLA: Thank you, Mr. Kraler.

98
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,560
Goodbye.

99
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:43,600
EDITH: Anne!
-lt's all right, l have on three more.

100
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,160
PETRONELLA:
Excuse me, Mr. Frank.

101
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:49,480
-What do they mean, ''13 minutes''?
-Before workmen come.

102
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,520
Now...

103
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:55,200
...while the men are in the building
below, we must be quiet.

104
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:59,600
Every sound can be heard down there,
in the offices and in the workrooms too.

105
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:02,840
The men come at about 8:30.
They leave at about 5:30.

106
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:06,440
So to be perfectly safe,
from 8 a.m. until 6 p.m...

107
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:10,040
...we must move about up here
only when absolutely necessary...

108
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,720
...and then in stockinged feet.

109
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:15,920
We must not speak above a whisper
or run any water.

110
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:19,640
We cannot use the sink or even,
forgive me, the W.C.

111
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,960
The pipes go down through
the workrooms. No trash must ever be--

112
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:26,880
[SIREN APPROACHING]

113
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:40,240
[SIREN FADES]

114
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:47,840
No trash, which might reveal someone's
living here. Not even a potato peeling.

115
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,360
We must burn everything
in the stove at night.

116
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:56,040
This is the way that we must live
until it is over, if we are to survive.

117
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:59,320
Until it is over.

118
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:02,880
After 6:OO, we can move about.
We can talk and laugh...

119
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:06,800
...have our supper, read, play games,
just as we would at home.

120
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:10,120
Now it would be wise
if we all went to our rooms...

121
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:14,440
...and were settled before 8:OO.
Mr. and Mrs. Van Daan, you're upstairs.

122
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:18,720
l regret there's no place up there
for Peter. But he'll be here, near us.

123
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:23,880
-And where am l?
-You and Margot will be in there.

124
