with two families.

465
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:50,960
But no, no, he had to ask them.

466
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,480
Shh.

467
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:04,280
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

468
00:42:08,640 --> 00:42:11,040
[KNOCKING]

469
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:14,720
Every time l hear that sound,
my heart stops.

470
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:17,640
MARGOT :
It's Miep. Father.

471
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:21,160
FRANK: Yes?
EDITH: It's Miep.

472
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:27,240
-Here's your list.
EDITH: Thank you.

473
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:29,040
VAN DAAN: Is it Miep?
-Yes.

474
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:33,040
-At last, l'll have some cigarettes.
-Miep's here.

475
00:42:33,680 --> 00:42:36,440
l can't tell you how sorry l am
about the coat.

476
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:38,520
Don't worry.

477
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,200
-Hello.
-Miep.

478
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:42,040
Mr. Kraler.

479
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:45,400
When Mr. Kraler comes,
the sun begins to shine.

480
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:48,120
-Dirk has had to leave.
-Dirk is Miep's fiancé.

481
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:52,080
He had to go into hiding in the country
to escape a labor call-up...

482
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:54,560
...but he has let me have
the radio for you.

483
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:58,920
-He shouldn't have.
-lt was too dangerous.

484
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:00,560
Look!

485
00:43:19,080 --> 00:43:23,360
[MUSIC PLAYS]

486
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:02,760
ANNE:
Our blessed radío.

487
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:06,920
lt gíves us our eyes and ears
out ínto the world.

488
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:10,080
We lísten to the German statíon
only for good musíc.

489
00:44:10,240 --> 00:44:12,080
MAN ON RADlO:
The Axís forces ín the Western....

490
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,840
ANNE:
And we lísten to the BBC for hope.

491
00:44:15,040 --> 00:44:20,680
MAN ON RADlO: --ceaseless attacks _y
Iand and aír forces are now ín full retreat.

492
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:25,040
The 8th army contínues
to advance.

493
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:26,720
PETRONELLA:
It's good.

494
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:31,720
All right, Peter. Now, let's see what
they have to say about the Nazis, huh?

495
00:44:35,920 --> 00:44:37,160
Berlin.

496
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:41,400
[MAN ON RADlO
SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

497
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:14,160
Must we listen?

498
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:19,040
All right, Peter, that's enough.

499
00:46:00,560 --> 00:46:02,520
The Green Police, they've found us.

500
00:47:12,840 --> 00:47:14,960
MAN :
Hmm.

501
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:36,400
[FLOOR SQUEAKS]

502
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:51,440
Hm.

503
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:03,800
[HUMS]

504
00:48:10,560 --> 00:48:12,120
Hm?

505
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:17,000
Hm.

506
00:48:38,880 --> 00:48:40,320
[SIREN WAILING]

507
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:42,880
[COUGHS]

508
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:53,440
[SIREN FADING]

509
00:49:31,720 --> 00:49:35,240
[CLOCK CHIMES]

510
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:04,400
[EXPLOSlONS IN DISTANCE]

511
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:25,760
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

512
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:41,040
MIEP:
This way, Mr. Dussel.

513
00:50:44,840 --> 00:50:48,360
[AIR RAID SIREN WAILS]

514
00:51:33,040 --> 00:51:35,040
[KNOCKS]

515
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:38,440
KRALER: It's Kraler.
MIEP: And Miep.

516
00:51:38,600 --> 00:51:42,360
KRALER: Please open.
PETRONELLA: Bless them. They're here.

517
00:51:42,520 --> 00:51:45,880
FRANK: Kraler?
KRALER: And Miep, yes. Open, please.

518
00:51:50,480 --> 00:51:54,080
-Well, we had a visitor last night.
-We had a visitor last night.

519
00:51:54,240 --> 00:51:55,720
-Yes, yes.
-A thief.

520
00:51:55,920 --> 00:51:57,840
-lt was a thief?
-Did you hear him?

521
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,680
-Yes.
-He was right under you.

522
00:51:59,880 --> 00:52:01,600
ln the office right under here.

523
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:05,200
EDITH: We did not know.
MARGOT: We thought it was the police.

524
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:09,680
-Are you sure, Miep?
-You were, of course, quiet?

525
00:52:10,280 --> 00:52:13,880
We didn't move.
We hardly breathed all night.

526
00:52:14,040 --> 00:52:17,840
-That is good. It was close.
-Too close.

527
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:20,760
He went through everything,
the desk and the files.

528
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:23,880
And he found the safe,
but he could not get it open.

529
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:27,400
He's looking for our ration card supply
from the underground.

530
00:52:27,560 --> 00:52:29,720
-Somebody knows.
-They are in that safe.

531
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:34,320
They'll come back. You should get rid
of that safe. Get it out of here.

532
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,520
Yes, put a sign on the door:

533
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:39,320
''Burglars do not come back.
The safe is gone.''

534
00:52:39,480 --> 00:52:42,040
-Jokes, yeah.
-Mr. Frank, l must talk to you.

535
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:44,960
-Of course.
-Maybe we should get rid of the radio.

536
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:49,040
Put it in the stove. Burn it.
If the Green Police found that radio....

537
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:51,840
Then they'd find her diary.
We'll burn that too.

538
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,040
Not my diary.
My diary goes, l go with it.

539
00:52:55,200 --> 00:52:56,840
-Where is it?
-Mr. Van Daan.

540
00:52:57,000 --> 00:53:00,040
lf they find us, they might as well
find the diary, the radio....

541
00:53:00,960 --> 00:53:03,920
-Usually, l try to bring good news.
-Yes, l know.

542
00:53:04,080 --> 00:53:06,560
But something has happened.
A man came to me.

543
00:53:06,720 --> 00:53:09,640
He told me that he has
a Jewish friend, a dentist.

544
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:14,560
He begged me, could l find him
a hiding place? So l have come to you.

545
00:53:14,720 --> 00:53:18,560
lt is a terrible thing to ask of you,
living the way you are...

546
00:53:18,720 --> 00:53:22,080
-...but could you take him in?
-Well, of course we will.

547
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:25,280
-His name is Jan Dussel.
-Dussel. l think l know him.

548
00:53:25,440 --> 00:53:27,880
EDITH: l think it's fine to have him.
-Thank you.

549
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:30,640
But, Otto, where are we going
to put him? Where?

550
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:35,560
-There's so little food as it is--
-We can stretch the food a little.

551
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:37,680
PETER: He can have my bed.
-No, thank you.

552
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:40,680
Margot will move in with us,
and he can have her bed.

553
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:42,200
MARGOT :
l'll get my things out.

554
00:54:10,600 --> 00:54:14,960
[BELL RINGS]

555
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:25,280
Mr. Dussel.

556
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:37,520
Don't bump your head.

557
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:43,560
Come in, Mr. Dussel.

558
00:54:44,040 --> 00:54:46,520
This is Mr. Frank.

559
00:54:46,680 --> 00:54:50,160
-Mr. Otto Frank?
-Yes. Let me have your things, please.

560
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:51,800
Thank you, Mr. Frank.

561
00:54:51,960 --> 00:54:54,040
l leave you in good hands.

562
00:54:54,200 --> 00:54:58,600
Mr. Dussel, l must return your coat.

563
00:55:00,680 --> 00:55:03,840
-What can l say to thank you?
-Mr. Kraler and Miep...

564
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:07,000
.. .they're our lifeline.
Without them, we couldn't live.

565
00:55:07,240 --> 00:55:10,680
KRALER: Please. You make us seem
very heroic. It isn't that at all.

566
00:55:10,840 --> 00:55:14,400
-We simply don't like the Nazis.
-l know, l know.

567
00:55:14,560 --> 00:55:18,240
''Nobody's going to tell us Dutchmen
what to do with our damn Jews.''

568
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:21,480
We'll be up tomorrow,
see if they're treating you right.

569
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:23,600
KRALER: Goodbye.
DUSSEL: Goodbye, Mr. Kraler.

570
00:55:23,760 --> 00:55:25,800
MIEP: Goodbye, Mr. Dussel.
DUSSEL: Goodbye, Miep.

571
00:55:26,320 --> 00:55:28,440
-Welcome, Mr. Dussel.
-Thank you.

572
00:55:28,600 --> 00:55:34,240
This is my wife, Edith.
Mr. and Mrs. Van Daan. Their son, Peter.

573
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:37,280
My daughters, Margot and Anne.

574
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:39,760
DUSSEL: Hello, Anne.
-How do you do?

575
00:55:39,960 --> 00:55:41,600
-Margot.
-How do you do?

576
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:44,680
Please, Mr. Dussel, sit down.

577
00:55:45,720 --> 00:55:47,400
Thank you.

578
00:55:48,480 --> 00:55:50,960
l'm dreaming, l know it.

579
00:55:51,120 --> 00:55:53,840
Mr. Otto Frank here.

580
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:59,480
You're not in Switzerland, then?
Someone said that you had escaped.

581
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:05,120
-And you've been here all this time?
-Ever since July.

582
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:10,560
Did Mr. Kraler warn you
you won't get much to eat here?

583
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:12,440
You can imagine.

584
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:15,800
Three ration cards
among the seven of us.

585
00:56:15,960 --> 00:56:18,240
Now you make eight.

586
00:56:19,520 --> 00:56:22,680
DUSSEL: Mr. Van Daan, you don't realize
what's happening outside...

587
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:26,400
...that you should warn me
of a thing like that.

588
00:56:27,440 --> 00:56:31,600
You don't realize what's going on,
right here in Amsterdam.

589
00:56:31,760 --> 00:56:34,400
Every day, hundreds of Jews disappear.

590
00:56:36,800 --> 00:56:42,040
They surround the block.
They search house by house.

591
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:48,280
Every day, children come home from
school to find their parents gone.

592
00:56:48,920 --> 00:56:51,640
Hundreds are being deported.

593
00:56:53,720 --> 00:56:58,040
People that you and l know:
the Hallensteins, the Wessels.

594
00:56:58,200 --> 00:56:59,440
EDITH :
Oh, no.

595
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:02,280
DUSSEL:
You get your call-up notice:

596
00:57:02,480 --> 00:57:06,480
Come to the station on such
and such a day and hour.

597
00:57:06,640 --> 00:57:09,360
Bring only what you can carry.''

598
00:57:09,640 --> 00:57:12,320
lf you don't, they come drag you
from your home...

599
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:15,520
...and ship you off to Mauthausen,
the death camp.

600
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:18,400
We didn't know that things
had got so much worse.

601
00:57:18,920 --> 00:57:22,080
Forgive me for speaking so.

602
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:24,760
Do you know the de Vries?

603
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:27,280
They're gone.

604
00:57:33,320 --> 00:57:36,280
Sanne and l are in the same class.

605
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:40,000
Sanne is my best--
My best friend.

606
00:57:40,400 --> 00:57:45,000
She returned home from school
to find her parents gone.

607
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:52,080
She was alone for two days,
and then they came and took her away.

608
00:57:53,760 --> 00:57:55,640
Gone?

609
00:58:02,320 --> 00:58:04,800
Yes, with all the others.

610
00:58:06,680 --> 00:58:08,560
Oh, no.

611
00:58:15,440 --> 00:58:17,840
People named Meyerberg,
they lived near us.

612
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:20,280
-Do you know--?
-We should put this off.

613
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:23,200
l'm sure Mr. Dussel would like
to get settled.

614
00:58:23,360 --> 00:58:25,640
Would you take Mr. Dussel
to his room now?

615
00:58:25,800 --> 00:58:28,800
ANNE:
If you'll come with me, Mr. Dussel.

616
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:36,720
Forgive me if l haven't expressed
my gratitude.

617
00:58:37,360 --> 00:58:40,680
This has been such a shock to me.

618
00:58:41,920 --> 00:58:46,720
l always thought of myself as Dutch.
l was born in Holland.

619
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:50,720
My father was born in Holland,
and my grandfather.

620
00:58:50,920 --> 00:58:55,480
And now, after all these years....

621
00:58:58,000 --> 00:59:00,480
lf you will excuse me.

622
00:59:07,480 --> 00:59:11,440
[MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

623
00:59:38,880 --> 00:59:42,440
lt's so different from what
Mr. Kraler tells us.

624
00:59:42,640 --> 00:59:45,440
Mr. Kraler says that things
are improving.

625
00:59:45,840 --> 00:59:49,280
l like it better the way Kraler tells it.

626
01:00:42,040 --> 01:00:44,360
Good night.

627
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:49,560
-Say good night!
-Good night, Mother.

628
01:00:54,560 --> 01:00:56,720
PETRONELLA: Good night, Mr. Frank.
FRANK: Good night.

629
01:01:01,040 --> 01:01:03,280
Do you have any children, Mr. Dussel?

630
01:01:03,440 --> 01:01:06,440
No, l never married.

631
01:01:10,640 --> 01:01:14,360
-Have you no family at all?
DUSSEL: No one.

632
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:20,440
ANNE:
How dreadful.

633
01:01:21,040 --> 01:01:23,920
You must be terribly lonely.

634
01:01:25,240 --> 01:01:27,360
l'm used to it.

635
01:01:27,520 --> 01:01:30,640
l don't think l could ever get used to it.

636
01:01:33,160 --> 01:01:34,840
Didn't you even have a pet?

637
01:01:35,040 --> 01:01:36,960
-A cat or a dog?
-No.

638
01:01:37,120 --> 01:01:41,520
No, no, l have an allergy
to furbearing animals.

639
01:01:41,680 --> 01:01:44,560
-Gives me asthma.
-Oh, dear.

640
01:01:44,760 --> 01:01:46,120
What?

641
01:01:47,080 --> 01:01:48,320
Peter has a cat.

642
01:01:49,640 --> 01:01:53,360
-He has? He has it here?
-Yes.

643
01:02:13,800 --> 01:02:15,720
We hardly ever see it.

644
01:02:15,880 --> 01:02:18,360
-He keeps it in his room all the time.
-Yeah.

645
01:02:18,520 --> 01:02:22,800
-l'm sure it'll be all right.
-Well, l hope so. Yes.

646
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:30,760
l hope l won't be too much
of a bother to you, Mr. Dussel.

647
01:02:30,920 --> 01:02:32,360
No.

648
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:35,960
l seem to be able to get
everyone's back up.

649
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:39,920
Oh, l always get along very well
with young people.

650
01:02:40,080 --> 01:02:42,640
My patients all bring
their children to me...

651
01:02:42,800 --> 01:02:45,960
...because they know l get along well
with them.

652
01:02:46,120 --> 01:02:48,840
So don't you worry about that.

653
01:02:49,760 --> 01:02:52,200
Thank you, Mr. Dussel.

654
01:02:52,800 --> 01:02:54,480
Good night.

655
01:02:55,120 --> 01:02:56,480
l'll be back.

656
01:02:56,640 --> 01:02:59,080
Good night, Mr. Dussel.

657
01:03:06,560 --> 01:03:08,480
Be careful.

658
01:03:12,480 --> 01:03:15,640
[CLATTERING]

659
01:03:30,200 --> 01:03:35,000
[BELL CHIMES]

660
01:04:33,840 --> 01:04:38,560
[MEN CHEERING FAINTLY]

661
01:04:58,960 --> 01:05:00,840
ANNE:
Sanne.

662
01:05:01,880 --> 01:05:03,560
Sanne?

663
01:05:04,520 --> 01:05:06,280
Sanne!

664
01:05:10,600 --> 01:05:13,360
[LAUGHING AND SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

665
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:22,400
[GUN SHOOTING]

666
01:05:32,760 --> 01:05:34,840
[SCREAMS]

667
01:05:35,000 --> 01:05:37,640
Save me! Save me! No, no!

668
01:05:38,320 --> 01:05:41,480
-No! Don't take me!
DUSSEL: Stop it! Stop it!

669
01:05:43,320 --> 01:05:46,240
[LAUGHING]

670
01:05:50,680 --> 01:05:52,200
ANNE:
Save me.

671
01:05:52,360 --> 01:05:55,960
EDITH: Hush, Annie, hush.
It's all right. It's all right.

672
01:05:56,120 --> 01:05:59,760
Please, Mr. Dussel, turn on the light.
It was just a dream.

673
01:05:59,960 --> 01:06:02,720
You're here, safe, you see?

674
01:06:02,920 --> 01:06:06,160
Something must be done with that child.
Yelling like that.

675
01:06:06,320 --> 01:06:09,920
Who knows who might be in the street?
She's endangering our lives.

676
01:06:10,080 --> 01:06:14,920
Mr. Dussel, after all, Anne is not
exactly a trained frontline soldier.

677
01:06:15,080 --> 01:06:17,960
Please, Mr. Dussel, go back to bed.

678
01:06:18,160 --> 01:06:22,400
She'll be herself in a minute or two,
won't you, Annie?

679
01:06:24,480 --> 01:06:26,760
DUSSEL:
Go back to bed. Hmph.

680
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:34,440
Excuse me. l'm going to the W.C.,
the one room where there's peace.

681
01:06:35,960 --> 01:06:37,680
FRANK:
Go back to bed now.

682
01:06:37,840 --> 01:06:40,320
EDITH :
Would you like some water?

683
01:06:41,600 --> 01:06:44,280
Was it a very bad dream?

684
01:06:44,920 --> 01:06:46,840
Perhaps if you told me?

685
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:50,080
l'd rather not talk about it.

686
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:51,720
EDITH :
Try to sleep, then.

687
01:06:53,320 --> 01:06:57,840
-l'll sit right here beside you.
ANNE: You don't have to.

688
01:06:58,880 --> 01:07:02,880
But l'd like to stay with you.
Very much, really.

689
01:07:03,080 --> 01:07:05,560
l'd rather you didn't.

690
01:07:11,400 --> 01:07:12,640
EDITH :
Good night--

691
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:22,040
You'll be all right?

692
01:07:22,880 --> 01:07:25,520
There's nothing that you want?

693
01:07:25,720 --> 01:07:28,920
Will you please ask Father to come?

694
01:07:34,360 --> 01:07:36,840
Yes, of course, Anne, dear.

695
01:07:45,080 --> 01:07:47,280
She asked for you.

696
01:07:49,160 --> 01:07:51,680
-Edith....
EDITH: Go to her, Otto.

697
01:07:51,840 --> 01:07:54,560
She's still trembling with fear.

698
01:08:13,520 --> 01:08:15,240
[CRYING]

699
01:08:15,440 --> 01:08:17,560
She wants nothing of me.

700
01:08:17,720 --> 01:08:20,400
She pulled away when l leaned down
to kiss her.

701
01:08:20,600 --> 01:08:24,280
They broke down the door and tried
to drag me out, the way they did Sanne.

702
01:08:24,440 --> 01:08:25,480
Anne.

703
01:08:26,480 --> 01:08:28,400
MARGOT :
It's just a phase.

704
01:08:28,560 --> 01:08:30,880
All girls turn to their fathers
at this age.

705
01:08:31,080 --> 01:08:33,360
They give all their love
to their fathers.

706
01:08:33,520 --> 01:08:38,040
EDITH: You weren't like this.
You didn't shut me out.

707
01:08:40,360 --> 01:08:42,000
So....

708
01:08:44,000 --> 01:08:48,600
-Do you want me to read to you?
-No, just sit with me for a minute.

709
01:08:49,440 --> 01:08:50,720
Was l awful?

710
01:08:50,880 --> 01:08:56,360
-Do you think anyone outside heard me?
-No. Now, lie down quietly so.

711
01:08:56,520 --> 01:08:59,840
Like this. Now try to sleep.

712
01:09:00,840 --> 01:09:03,400
l'm a terrible coward.

713
01:09:03,800 --> 01:09:06,920
l'm so disappointed in myself.

714
01:09:08,600 --> 01:09:10,720
l think l'm really grown-up...

715
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:14,800
...and then something happens,
and l run to you like a baby.

716
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:18,000
l love you, Father.
l don't love anyone but you.

717
01:09:18,200 --> 01:09:20,960
-Annele. Annele.
ANNE: It's true.

718
01:09:21,120 --> 01:09:23,400
You're the only one l love.

719
01:09:24,520 --> 01:09:27,600
l've been thinking about it
for a long time.

720
01:09:28,400 --> 01:09:29,920
FRANK:
It's fine.

721
01:09:30,080 --> 01:09:32,920
lt's fine to have you tell me
that you love me...

722
01:09:33,080 --> 01:09:37,080
...but l'd be much happier if you said
that you loved your mother as well.

723
01:09:37,240 --> 01:09:40,080
She needs your help so much.

724
01:09:41,120 --> 01:09:42,560
Your love.

725
01:09:42,720 --> 01:09:46,720
We have nothing in common.
She doesn't understand me.

726
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:51,080
Whenever l try to explain my views
on life, she asks me if l'm constipated.

727
01:09:52,520 --> 01:09:55,040
You hurt her very much just now.
She's crying.

728
01:09:55,680 --> 01:09:57,080
She is in there crying.

729
01:10:06,200 --> 01:10:10,760
Oh, Father, l was horrible, wasn't l?

730
01:10:10,920 --> 01:10:13,840
What's the matter with me?
Tell me.

731
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:17,280
Don't say it's just a phase.
Help me.

732
01:10:19,760 --> 01:10:23,960
There is so little that we parents can do
to help our children, Annie.

733
01:10:24,120 --> 01:10:28,760
We can only try to set a good example,
point the way.

734
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:31,760
The rest you must do yourself.

735
01:10:32,280 --> 01:10:36,040
ANNIE:
l'm trying. Really, l am.

736
01:10:36,200 --> 01:10:41,080
Every night, l think back over all the things
l did that day that were wrong.

737
01:10:41,680 --> 01:10:44,680
Like putting the wet mop
in Mrs. Van Daan's bed.

738
01:10:48,600 --> 01:10:50,960
And now this with Mother.

739
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:54,120
l say to myself, ''That was wrong.''

740
01:10:54,280 --> 01:10:59,080
And l make up my mind never
to do that again. Never.

741
01:10:59,920 --> 01:11:02,920
l may do something worse,
but l'll never do that again.

742
01:11:04,080 --> 01:11:06,840
l have a nicer side, Father...

743
01:11:07,080 --> 01:11:09,560
...but l'm scared to show it.

744
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:13,000
l'm afraid people will laugh at me.

745
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:18,480
So the mean Anne comes
to the outside...

746
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:22,240
...and the good Anne stays
in the inside.

747
01:11:23,840 --> 01:11:27,280
And l keep on trying
to switch them around...

748
01:11:27,440 --> 01:11:30,360
...have the good Anne outside...

749
01:11:30,760 --> 01:11:33,480
...and the bad Anne inside.

750
01:11:35,000 --> 01:11:37,480
lt would be what l'd like to be.

751
01:11:39,120 --> 01:11:40,920
And might be.

752
01:11:41,880 --> 01:11:43,840
lf only....

753
01:12:05,360 --> 01:12:07,320
She's asleep.

754
01:13:14,680 --> 01:13:19,680
ANNE:
Thursday. the 29th of October. 19$2.

755
01:13:19,840 --> 01:13:23,360
Mr. Dussel and l had
a great battle yesterday.

756
01:13:23,840 --> 01:13:26,240
Yes. Mr. Dussel.

757
