774
01:15:08,880 --> 01:15:12,680
lt's too much.
It's just too much.

775
01:15:19,920 --> 01:15:21,680
Suppose they hit this house?

776
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:24,360
What will we do?
We can't go out in the street.

777
01:15:24,520 --> 01:15:25,920
What will we do?

778
01:15:26,120 --> 01:15:29,800
lf they hit this house,
your worries will be over.

779
01:15:35,480 --> 01:15:39,200
That big explosion,
an English plane fell right in this block!

780
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:41,000
Peter.

781
01:15:43,760 --> 01:15:45,400
Peter!

782
01:15:56,480 --> 01:15:59,240
FRANK: It's far away from here.
VAN DAAN: Please don't.

783
01:15:59,440 --> 01:16:00,640
FRANK:
Just look at them.

784
01:16:00,800 --> 01:16:03,480
Mrs. Van Daan,
this should be music to your ears.

785
01:16:03,640 --> 01:16:04,760
-Music?
FRANK: Of course.

786
01:16:04,960 --> 01:16:08,160
The more planes they send,
the sooner the war will be over.

787
01:16:08,320 --> 01:16:12,360
-The sooner we'll be home again.
-l don't believe it'll ever be over.

788
01:16:14,000 --> 01:16:16,800
Do you know what l'd like right now?
A cup of tea.

789
01:16:16,960 --> 01:16:18,640
Oh, yes, please.

790
01:16:18,840 --> 01:16:21,000
You can't have tea, then,
for breakfast.

791
01:16:21,160 --> 01:16:23,760
lf you have it now,
you won't have any tomorrow.

792
01:16:23,920 --> 01:16:25,600
-l don't care.
-Neither do l.

793
01:16:25,800 --> 01:16:26,840
Me too, please.

794
01:16:28,120 --> 01:16:31,520
How about you, Mr. Dussel?
Tea now or tomorrow morning?

795
01:16:31,720 --> 01:16:34,600
-Tomorrow morning.
-Sure?

796
01:16:34,760 --> 01:16:36,320
Sure.

797
01:16:42,520 --> 01:16:43,840
l'll take mine now.

798
01:16:44,480 --> 01:16:46,240
The skylight!

799
01:16:46,680 --> 01:16:48,560
FRANK:
Edith, come!

800
01:16:49,320 --> 01:16:50,520
PETRONELLA:
Oh, Peter!

801
01:16:50,760 --> 01:16:53,600
Peter! Peter!

802
01:16:54,040 --> 01:16:55,720
Peter!

803
01:16:58,840 --> 01:17:00,440
Peter!

804
01:17:51,040 --> 01:17:54,080
FRANK: ''Praised be thou, Lord,
ruler of the universe...

805
01:17:54,240 --> 01:17:56,880
...who's sanctified us
with thy commandments...

806
01:17:57,040 --> 01:18:00,160
...and bidden us kindle
the Hannukah lights.

807
01:18:00,360 --> 01:18:04,240
Praised be thou, O, Lord, our God,
ruler of the universe...

808
01:18:04,400 --> 01:18:09,480
.. .who wrought wondrous deliverances
for our fathers in days of old.

809
01:18:09,640 --> 01:18:12,800
Praised be thou, O, Lord, our God,
ruler of the universe...

810
01:18:13,000 --> 01:18:15,760
...that thou hast given us life
and sustenance...

811
01:18:15,960 --> 01:18:19,040
...and brought us to this happy season.''
Amen.

812
01:18:19,240 --> 01:18:21,080
-Amen.
-Amen.

813
01:18:21,240 --> 01:18:25,120
ANNE:
Monday. the 7th of December. 19$2.

814
01:18:25,280 --> 01:18:27,960
The Hannukah holíday
came early thís year.

815
01:18:28,120 --> 01:18:29,960
''We kindle this Hannukah light...

816
01:18:30,120 --> 01:18:33,560
...to celebrate the wonderful deeds
wrought through the zeal...

817
01:18:33,720 --> 01:18:38,640
...with which God filled the hearts of
the heroic Maccabees 2000 years ago.

818
01:18:38,800 --> 01:18:40,720
They fought against indifference.. .

819
01:18:40,880 --> 01:18:45,120
.. .against tyranny and oppression,
and they restored our temple to us.

820
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:48,640
May these lights remind us
that we should ever look to God...

821
01:18:48,800 --> 01:18:51,560
...whence cometh our help.''
Amen.

822
01:18:51,720 --> 01:18:53,680
-Amen.
-Amen.

823
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:04,080
l lift up mine eyes unto the mountains
from whence cometh my help.

824
01:19:04,240 --> 01:19:07,720
My help cometh from the Lord,
who made heaven and earth.

825
01:19:07,880 --> 01:19:10,280
He will not suffer thy foot
to be moved.

826
01:19:10,480 --> 01:19:12,920
He that keepeth thee will not slumber.

827
01:19:13,080 --> 01:19:17,280
He that keepeth Israel doth
neither slumber nor sleep.

828
01:19:17,680 --> 01:19:19,240
The Lord is thy keeper.

829
01:19:19,440 --> 01:19:22,320
The Lord is thy shade
upon thy right hand.

830
01:19:22,680 --> 01:19:27,600
The Lord shall keep thee from all evil.
He shall keep thy soul.

831
01:19:27,760 --> 01:19:31,800
The Lord shall guard thy going out
and thy coming in...

832
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:35,800
...from this time forth and forevermore.''
Amen.

833
01:19:36,000 --> 01:19:37,720
-Amen.
-Amen.

834
