EDITH :
l remember particularly the candles.

846
01:20:06,000 --> 01:20:09,000
First one, as we have tonight.
The second night, two.

847
01:20:09,200 --> 01:20:12,840
The next night, three, and so on,
until eight candles are burning.

848
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:16,800
When there are eight candles,
it's truly beautiful.

849
01:20:16,960 --> 01:20:21,200
What l remember best are the presents
we used to get, eight days of presents.

850
01:20:21,360 --> 01:20:23,360
Each day, they got better and better.

851
01:20:23,520 --> 01:20:27,200
We are all here, alive.
That's present enough.

852
01:20:27,680 --> 01:20:29,840
No, it isn't.
l've got something.

853
01:20:30,000 --> 01:20:31,440
What is it?

854
01:20:35,920 --> 01:20:38,040
-Presents.
-Real presents?

855
01:20:38,200 --> 01:20:39,720
-She made it herself.
-Look!

856
01:20:39,880 --> 01:20:42,960
-lsn't it festive? Isn't it gay?
-Oh, it's beautiful.

857
01:20:43,880 --> 01:20:45,720
For Margot.

858
01:20:52,640 --> 01:20:54,720
Read it out loud.

859
01:20:56,920 --> 01:20:59,720
You have never lost your temper

860
01:20:59,880 --> 01:21:01,400
You never wíll l fear

861
01:21:01,560 --> 01:21:04,560
You are so good
