Let's see what it is.

864
01:21:10,000 --> 01:21:12,600
lt's a new crossword-puzzle book.

865
01:21:12,800 --> 01:21:16,440
lt's one you've done, but l rubbed it out.
If you wait and forget...

866
01:21:16,640 --> 01:21:19,240
...you can do it all over again!

867
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:21,480
-lt's wonderful.
-Clever.

868
01:21:21,640 --> 01:21:23,280
Thank you.

869
01:21:25,760 --> 01:21:28,040
For Mrs. Van Daan.

870
01:21:28,560 --> 01:21:32,280
Oh, l feel terrible.
l don't have a thing for anybody.

871
01:21:36,120 --> 01:21:37,320
lt's hair shampoo.

872
01:21:37,480 --> 01:21:41,640
l took all the bits of soap and mixed
them with the last of my toilet water.

873
01:21:41,800 --> 01:21:44,640
-Oh, thank you, Anneke!
-She's got your number.

874
01:21:44,800 --> 01:21:48,920
l wanted to write a poem for all of them,
but l didn't have time.

875
01:21:49,080 --> 01:21:51,640
Yours, Mr. Van Daan,
is really something.

876
01:21:52,040 --> 01:21:55,440
Something you want
more than anything.

877
01:22:02,240 --> 01:22:03,320
Cigarettes!

878
01:22:04,560 --> 01:22:05,600
Look at that!

879
01:22:05,760 --> 01:22:07,600
-Cigarettes!
-Two of them.

880
01:22:07,760 --> 01:22:12,240
Father found some pipe tobacco in the
pocket of his coat, and we made them.

881
01:22:12,400 --> 01:22:14,640
Rather, Father did.

882
01:22:15,840 --> 01:22:17,880
