my roommate, Mr. Dussel.

928
01:25:01,280 --> 01:25:03,360
Something for me?

929
01:25:10,520 --> 01:25:12,960
-Capsules.
-They're earplugs.

930
01:25:13,120 --> 01:25:17,040
To put in your ears so you won't
hear me when l thrash around at night.

931
01:25:17,200 --> 01:25:21,480
l made them myself. Try them.
See if you can hear me.

932
01:25:24,320 --> 01:25:25,880
-Watch him.
-Wait, l'll put--

933
01:25:26,040 --> 01:25:29,160
-Like that? Is that what you mean?
-Are you ready?

934
01:25:29,320 --> 01:25:31,520
-What?
-Are you ready?

935
01:25:31,800 --> 01:25:33,760
They work!

936
01:25:41,320 --> 01:25:42,960
They went in!
They went in!

937
01:25:43,120 --> 01:25:45,080
He can't get them out.

938
01:25:45,280 --> 01:25:49,400
What's the matter with you?
Get them out. Take them out.

939
01:25:49,720 --> 01:25:51,400
l got it.

940
01:25:53,320 --> 01:25:54,760
Thank you.

941
01:25:55,000 --> 01:25:57,160
-That's a real Hannukah.
-lsn't she cute?

942
01:25:57,320 --> 01:26:00,080
-A real Hannukah.
-Now let's sing the song, Father.

943
01:26:00,240 --> 01:26:02,920
Wait till you hear the Hannukah song,
Mr. Dussel.

944
01:26:03,120 --> 01:26:05,520
[ANNE SINGS]

945
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:08,800
Annele. l'm afraid we shouldn't
sing the song.

946
01:26:09,000 --> 01:26:11,560
lt's a song of jubilation
and of rejoicing.

947
01:26:11,720 --> 01:26:14,200
One is apt to become
too enthusiastic about it.

948
01:26:14,360 --> 01:26:16,920
ANNE: Please, let's sing it.
l promise not to shout.

949
01:26:17,080 --> 01:26:19,560
Very well, but quietly, Annie.
l'll keep my eye on you. If you get--

950
01:26:19,720 --> 01:26:21,920
Oh. Oh!

951
01:26:22,800 --> 01:26:26,880
l told you not to come in with that cat.
Get out of here!

952
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:32,400
What's the matter with you?
Haven't you any sense?

953
01:26:32,560 --> 01:26:34,560
-Get that cat out of here.
-Cat?

954
01:26:34,720 --> 01:26:37,640
You heard me, get it out of here!

955
01:26:40,160 --> 01:26:42,240
l have no cat.

956
01:26:42,400 --> 01:26:44,400
Mr. Dussel.

957
01:26:46,240 --> 01:26:49,920
lt doesn't have to be the cat.
Just the hairs on his clothing...

958
01:26:50,080 --> 01:26:53,280
...from the cat is enough
when he comes in the room.

959
01:26:53,440 --> 01:26:56,480
You won't be bothered anymore.
We're getting rid of it.

960
01:26:56,640 --> 01:26:58,120
At last, you listen to me.

961
01:26:58,280 --> 01:27:01,920
And l'm not doing it for you.
That's all in your mind, all of it.

962
01:27:02,080 --> 01:27:06,320
l'm doing it because l'm sick
of seeing that cat eat all our food.

963
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:08,800
That's not true.
l only give him scraps.

964
01:27:09,120 --> 01:27:12,840
Don't tell me.
He gets fatter every day.

965
01:27:13,040 --> 01:27:16,560
Damn cat looks better than any of us.
Out he goes tonight.

966
01:27:16,760 --> 01:27:17,800
No!

967
01:27:18,000 --> 01:27:20,880
Mr. Van Daan, you can't do that.
That's Peter's cat.

968
01:27:21,040 --> 01:27:23,680
-Peter loves that cat.
EDITH: Annie.

969
01:27:25,240 --> 01:27:27,000
lf he goes, l go.

970
01:27:27,520 --> 01:27:29,040
Go. Go.

971
01:27:29,240 --> 01:27:33,440
He's not going and the cat's not going.
What's wrong with you? It's Hannukah.

972
01:27:33,640 --> 01:27:36,400
Look, please, Annie, sing.

973
01:27:36,720 --> 01:27:39,120
[ANNE SINGS]

974
01:27:39,600 --> 01:27:41,040
Annele. Annele.

975
01:27:41,200 --> 01:27:44,360
l think we should first
blow out the candles.

976
01:27:44,520 --> 01:27:46,520
Then we'll have something
for tomorrow night.

977
01:27:46,680 --> 01:27:50,320
Father, you're supposed to let it
burn itself out.

978
01:27:50,480 --> 01:27:52,960
l'm sure that God
understands shortages.

979
01:27:53,160 --> 01:27:55,720
Praised be thou, Lord,
who has permitted us...

980
01:27:55,880 --> 01:27:58,240
.. .to celebrate this joyous festival.
Amen.

981
01:27:58,400 --> 01:28:00,200
-Amen.
-Amen.

982
01:28:06,800 --> 01:28:10,240
[FAINT CLATTERING]

983
01:28:43,480 --> 01:28:46,160
[GLASS SHATTERS]

984
01:31:15,760 --> 01:31:19,400
[CAT MEOWS]
[CRASHING]

985
01:31:39,640 --> 01:31:42,880
-l think they've gone.
-They've found us.

986
01:31:43,040 --> 01:31:45,280
lf they had, they would be
up here by now.

987
01:31:45,480 --> 01:31:49,720
l know it was the Green Police.
They've gone to get help.

988
01:31:49,880 --> 01:31:52,000
Maybe the Gestapo
Iooking for papers.

989
01:31:52,160 --> 01:31:54,160
Or another thief looking
for money.

990
01:32:03,120 --> 01:32:04,960
l'm going down.

991
01:32:05,480 --> 01:32:07,080
They may still be there.

992
01:32:07,240 --> 01:32:08,720
Annele, this is Saturday.

993
01:32:08,920 --> 01:32:13,200
We won't know what happened until
Miep or Mr. Kraler come here on Monday.

994
01:32:13,360 --> 01:32:17,360
We cannot live with this uncertainty.
Now, please. Please.

995
01:32:39,840 --> 01:32:43,320
Get our money.
They say you can buy them off.

996
01:32:43,480 --> 01:32:45,680
-Quick, go get the money.
-Keep still!

997
01:32:45,880 --> 01:32:48,640
You want to be dragged off
to a concentration camp?

998
01:32:48,800 --> 01:32:51,240
You gonna stand there
till they come get you?

999
01:32:51,400 --> 01:32:53,360
Will you keep still?

1000
01:33:11,240 --> 01:33:13,720
Someone go
and make Father come back.

1001
01:33:23,480 --> 01:33:27,320
VAN DAAN: Haven't you done enough?
ANNE: Please, Mr. Van Daan.

1002
01:33:32,960 --> 01:33:34,680
Annie!

1003
01:33:53,960 --> 01:33:58,480
EDITH: l lift up mine eyes unto the
mountains, from whence cometh my help.

1004
01:33:58,640 --> 01:34:02,240
My help cometh from the Lord,
who made heaven and earth.

1005
01:34:41,000 --> 01:34:43,440
He that keepeth thee will not slumber.

1006
01:34:43,600 --> 01:34:47,680
He that keepeth Israel
doth neither slumber nor sleep.

1007
01:34:47,840 --> 01:34:49,680
The Lord is thy keeper.

1008
01:34:49,840 --> 01:34:52,400
The Lord is thy shade
upon thy right hand.

1009
01:35:07,240 --> 01:35:08,440
Over here.

1010
01:35:17,160 --> 01:35:19,200
[SPEAKS IN GERMAN]

1011
01:35:37,160 --> 01:35:40,640
-l better go and look and make sure.
-Yeah.

1012
01:35:54,160 --> 01:35:56,560
The Lord shall keep thee from all evil.

1013
01:35:56,720 --> 01:35:59,400
-He shall keep thy soul.
VAN DAAN: Hear me, O, Israel.

1014
01:35:59,560 --> 01:36:04,000
The Lord shall guide thy going out
and thy coming in.

1015
01:36:11,120 --> 01:36:14,600
Took the typewriter and ran away.
He didn't shut the street door.

1016
01:36:14,760 --> 01:36:18,200
lt was swinging wide open.
The watchman was passing.

1017
01:39:35,920 --> 01:39:38,800
[SPEAKS IN GERMAN]

1018
01:40:48,520 --> 01:40:51,400
[MEOWING]

1019
01:40:55,720 --> 01:40:58,720
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

1020
01:41:05,520 --> 01:41:08,600
We had a burglar.
He got out as he heard me coming.

1021
01:41:27,480 --> 01:41:30,080
WATCHMAN :
l will lock the door and report it.

1022
01:41:40,000 --> 01:41:43,760
PETER: They've gone and locked the door.
EDITH: Oh, thank God, they've gone.

1023
01:41:43,920 --> 01:41:47,360
l'd just as soon they take us
than to continue with this agony.

1024
01:41:48,200 --> 01:41:50,400
l can't think.

1025
01:41:50,560 --> 01:41:52,720
lt's all right.
The danger has passed.

1026
01:41:52,920 --> 01:41:55,000
Who says the danger has passed?

1027
01:41:55,160 --> 01:41:58,240
Don't you realize that we're
in greater danger than ever?

1028
01:41:58,400 --> 01:42:00,240
Please, will you keep still?

1029
01:42:00,400 --> 01:42:04,440
Thanks to this clumsy fool,
someone now knows we're up here.

1030
01:42:04,640 --> 01:42:07,640
-Someone knows we're hiding.
-lt's a thief! You think...

1031
01:42:07,800 --> 01:42:11,360
...he'll go to the Green Police
and say, ''l was robbing a place...

1032
01:42:11,560 --> 01:42:14,560
...and l heard a noise above my head''?
Would he do that?

1033
01:42:14,720 --> 01:42:16,400
-l think he will.
-You're crazy.

1034
01:42:16,600 --> 01:42:19,480
l think that someday that the thief
will be caught...

1035
01:42:19,640 --> 01:42:22,320
...and he'll make
a bargain with the Gestapo.

1036
01:42:22,480 --> 01:42:25,040
He'll say to the Gestapo,
''lf you let me off...

1037
01:42:25,240 --> 01:42:27,640
...l'll show you where some Jews
are hiding.''

1038
01:42:27,800 --> 01:42:29,640
-That's what l think.
-Oh.

1039
01:42:29,800 --> 01:42:31,400
He's right.

1040
01:42:31,560 --> 01:42:35,600
MARGOT: Oh, Mother, let's get out
of here. We can't stay here now.

1041
01:42:35,760 --> 01:42:40,520
ANNE: Please, let's go.
-Go? Where?

1042
01:42:44,000 --> 01:42:46,520
Yes, where?

1043
01:42:48,120 --> 01:42:51,080
Have we lost all faith?

1044
01:42:51,240 --> 01:42:53,040
All courage?

1045
01:42:53,200 --> 01:42:56,560
A few moments ago, we thought they
had come for us, didn't we?

1046
01:42:56,720 --> 01:43:01,480
We thought it was the end. Well, it
wasn't the end. We're alive. We're safe.

1047
01:43:01,960 --> 01:43:05,320
We thank thee, O, Lord, our God,
that in thy infinite mercy...

1048
01:43:05,520 --> 01:43:08,000
...thou hast again seen fit
to spare us.

1049
01:43:08,200 --> 01:43:11,920
-Amen.
-Amen.

1050
01:43:15,640 --> 01:43:18,120
Annele.

1051
01:43:18,280 --> 01:43:21,720
The song.

1052
01:43:21,920 --> 01:43:24,840
How about the song?

1053
01:43:25,600 --> 01:43:29,400
[ANNE SINGS]

1054
01:43:38,440 --> 01:43:41,800
[ALL SINGING]

1055
01:44:13,400 --> 01:44:15,720
-Happy Hannukah.
-Happy Hannukah.

1056
01:44:17,800 --> 01:44:20,920
[BELLS RINGING]

1057
01:44:44,920 --> 01:44:50,080
ANNE:
Saturday. the 1st of January. 19$$.

1058
01:44:50,240 --> 01:44:52,840
Another new year has begun.. .

1059
01:44:53,000 --> 01:44:57,800
.. .and we fínd ourselves stíll
ín our hídíng place.

1060
01:45:00,960 --> 01:45:02,640
We have been here now.. .

1061
01:45:02,800 --> 01:45:08,280
.. .for one year.
fíve months and 25 days.

1062
01:45:08,800 --> 01:45:12,240
One of our famíly has left us.

1063
01:45:12,400 --> 01:45:15,200
Mouschí ran away.

1064
01:45:16,600 --> 01:45:19,480
We're all a líttle thínner.

1065
01:45:19,640 --> 01:45:24,400
The Van Daans' díscussíons
